 A RETIRED Secretary General of Kagara Hospital, Mr. Joshua Twaki has been killed and nine others, including a six-month-old kidnapped in an attack by armed bandits in Kagara, headquarters of Rafi Local Government Area of Niger State. The incident occurred on Tuesday. Sources said bandits came motorcycles shooting rapidly. Police spokesman Wasiu Abiodun confirmed the attack, saying the Commissioner of Police Adamu Usman has dispatched a crack team to the area to secure the residents. Abiodun stated that the police are on top of the situation calling on the people not to panic as the security agencies are on ground to protect them. 